metadata.name: Harmony
metadata.description:
Title: Harmony

Artist: XArtSup

Location: Valley Forge National Park, King of Prussia, PA, USA

Nature has a calming quality that can help us to relax and reconnect with ourselves. Being mindful of nature can help us to find peace and harmony within ourselves and with the world around us.  By connecting with nature, we can experience a sense of balance and harmony with the world. We can also gain a deeper understanding of the natural world and how it works, as well as an appreciation for the beauty and diversity of the environment. Valley Forge National park is one place where we will find peace & harmony.

Valley Forge National Historical Park is the site of the third winter encampment of the Continental Army during the American Revolutionary War, taking place from December 19, 1777, to June 19, 1778.
